							<a name="Plane of Fear Follow up">Plane of Fear Follow up
					</td>
					<td align="right">
						<font face="verdana" color="#6B5A39" size="-2">
						Sunday, May&nbsp;13
					</td>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<font face="verdana" color="#BFBFBF" size="-1">
						<div align="justify">
							Only a bit late but here is a follow up for our excellent time in Plane of Fear! We had an almost flawless break in with very few deaths. Many thanks to those on the FD team who sacraficed themselves while trying to do their job. Many thanks also to those on the pull team who took so many DTs while working around Fright, Dread, and Terror. In the end we got all three golems, who are on par and even tougher than the old Cazic-Thule with only ONE whipeout the entire night!<br><br>

Although loot was a bit slow here it is. Cryosilk Collar: Garrissa, Voltaeus; Shiverback Jerkin: Daimyo; Blighted Gloves: Ashnar; Umbral Bracer: Huughruhruu; Fluxbladed Axe: Mitivo; Blighted Arms: Ashnar; Umbral Legs: Kinnayar; Slime Blood of Cazic-Thule: Mardia; Staff of the Earth Crafters(sp?): Kiriin; Vermiculated Gloves: Gladewalker, Getchathere; Carmine Hat: Voltaeus; Carmine Boots: Voltaeus; Ball of Everliving Golem: Jobob; Bloodfire: Cymric; Indocolite Gloves: Cuhulain; Umbral Arms: Huughruhruu; Blue Diamond: Meadmid<br><br>

On another note the <a href="rules.asp">Rules</a> and <a href="joining.asp">Joining</a> pages were updated to reflect our latest meeting.
							<br>~ <a href="mailto:Boisvertbladesong@hotmail.com">Boisvert</a><br><br>
							<center><hr size="1" color="#6B5A39" width="200"><center>
						</div>
